1 (a) "Application fee" means the total amount an applicant shall pay to be considered for renting the
2 premises.
3 (b) "Cost" means the out-of-pocket expense to a landlord or manager for a specific service in
4 relation to the application performed prior to approval or disapproval of a tenant, including but not limited to a
5 credit check. The term does not include a fee for the landlord or manager's time or effort for arranging or
6 performing the service.
7
8 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
9 integral part of Title 70, chapter 24, part 1, and the provisions of Title 70, chapter 24, part 1, apply to [section 1].
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Applicability. [This act] applies to an application fee collected by a
12 landlord or manager from an applicant on or after [the effective date of this act].
